property.description:
Welcome to The Riggins, Dunshaughlin; An exceptional A-rated Smart-House, set amidst the history rich countryside of Co. Meath on a site of c. 1 acre and boasting an internal area of c. 2,917 sq. ft.


Seldom does an opportunity arise to purchase such a superior country residence in a blissful rural setting, yet still within a short drive of surrounding towns, including Ashbourne (14-minute drive), Ratoath (8-minute drive) and Dunshaughlin (10-minute drive). The M3 and M2 motorways are both also within easy reach, as well as Dublin Airport, which is an approximate 29-minute drive away.


Built c. five years ago to a very high specification, this 5-bedroom property was built proudly and meticulously by its current owner, who ensured that no expense was spared to create a family home with modern conveniences and features, to include a Smart-Home system, security system with 360 degree cameras and underfloor heating, to name a few. Particular attention has been paid to energy efficiency, to include features such as a Heat Recovery System, Air to Water Heating, Triple / Double glazing throughout, double insulated walls and individual thermostat controls in every room.


To the front of the property are electric gates with an intercom system, which lead on to the driveway. Well-kept lawns extending to c. 1 acre surround the property and there is ample space for parking, outdoor entertaining and even a game of football for children!


On entering the front door, you arrive in the spacious entrance lobby area, which opens up on to the kitchen; an amazing sized open plan room, ideal for entertaining. This room includes a dining area, vaulted ceiling, centre island with Quartz worktop and a central bar / wine cooler storage feature, which separates the living area. Steps lead down to the living area, which boasts a wall insert wood burner for chillier evenings and also a wonderful focal point. There are two sets of sliding patio doors leading to the garden, as well as large floor to ceiling windows; a lovely addition throughout the property.


Opposite the kitchen is a second living room, ideal for a play area. There is also a large utility / laundry room. Off the lobby area, around to the right of the property is a hallway where the downstairs bathroom, two bedrooms (one ensuite), home office and walk-in storage cupboard are located. A feature solid timber floating staircase with steel frame leads to the upper level of the property.


Upstairs there are three bedrooms. The master bedroom boasts an integrated floating bed, fitted wardrobes & fitted storage solutions and a spacious ensuite bathroom with walk-in shower & free-standing bath. The further two upstairs bedrooms benefit from a Jack & Jill bathroom.


Outside, the property is surrounded with immaculately kept lawns. Landscaping plans are available upon request.


Properties of this size and calibre in such a wonderful location do not come to the market very often, so viewing comes very highly recommended. Contact DNG Tormey Lee on 01 835 7089. Viewings are strictly by appointment only.
